guration (e.g. edge density), probably by exploiting low\u2010contrast edges (i.e. closed canopy forest patches embedded in secondary forest) while foraging and travelling between higher quality resource patches.\n                \n                \n                  \n                    Synthesis and applications.\n                    Species\u2010 and ensemble\u2010specific responses to aspects of landscape structure suggest that both compositional and configurational aspects need to be managed effectively in conservation planning. However, conservation decisions based on associations of biodiversity metrics (e.g. richness, diversity and rarity) with landscape structure may be problematic as they are composite characteristics that mask individual responses and potentially reflect only patterns of the dominant species or groups.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Klingbeil, Brian T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Willig, Michael R.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/f310f089024e60fb38526ab11b60937c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/49f46c543dde6020fe491f1c3823accccebba01bb6918e10a6b0fb47eb2c4ff1", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/ZT4UGS2L", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/ZT4UGS2L", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/d7f1a11e7de2176874076f8c9d531dda!/b111155-113645", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:k